Parent class
child class


a mechanism which one class(child class) acquires the properties of other class(parent class)


Inheritence
Aggregation


Inheritence  : IS- A relationship

Dog(chlid class)
Animal(parent class)


Dog IS-A animal


Code reusabilty
Method overriding(polymorphism)




Types Of Inheritence

1> Single Inheritence

    class A (Parent class)  -a
       |
    class B (child class)  -b,a
    
2> Multilevel Inheritence
    
     class A    -a
       | 
     class B    -b,a
       |
     class C    -c,b,a
        |
     class D    -d,c,b,a
   
3> Hierarchichal


          		  A  -a 
          		  |
   --------------------------------
   |               |               |
   B-b,a           C-c,a           D-d,a 
   

4> Multiple


             A-a,d                B-b,d
              |                   |
              ---------------------
                        |
                        C-c,a,b
        
        
     -Interface
     
 5> Hybrid 
 
 			A -a 
          	|
   -----------------
   |               |               
   B-b,a           C-c,a           
   |                |
   ------------------
            |
            D-b,c,a                     
            
            
            
 Person(parent) -name
 Employee(child) - id,salary, dsgn, org
 
 Employee IS A person
 
 
 Animal<- Dog  <- BabyDog
 
 Animal
 |-Dog
 |-Cat
 
 
Hierachical Inheritence

Employee -id, salary, name
AdminEmployee extend employee-  dsgn   ;  insert(),display()
TechEmployee extend employee-bonus     ;  insert(),display()

main class
Switch cases
